    "collaborative settings like open source require a framework centered on cognitive demands and outcomes, as contributors voluntarily self-select based on the nature of cognitive tasks (Felin and Zenger 2014).",
    "This research identifies two distinct collaborative innovation patterns that anchor different ends of this cognitive spectrum, differing in knowledge search strategies and resultant competence outcomes (March 1991; Gatignon et al. 2002).",
    "The first innovation pattern, what we call as capability innovation, involves a search process focused seeking knowledge beyond the project's current domains and acquiring new competence.",
    "The second pattern, what we call as iterative innovation, involves a search process centered on enhancing understanding within existing knowledge domains and enhancing existing competence.",
    "2 In collaborative environments like open-source, capability innovation often requires \"question ingenuity\"the cognitive ability to identify entirely new problem spaces worth exploring before trying to generate solutions."
  ],
